Okay. This is bad. I am telling my entire damn life to a text box on a webpage. I have left Kevin, and I am now dating Mark. I don't know how good that is. There is a spark there between Mark, and I that was lacking when I was with Kevin. I am going to the dance on Thursday. I got my ticket today. I am going alone... which kinda makes me mad. Well, yeah. I am going to meet up with some of my friends before I go, so at least I'll have someone there to talk to you.

I really like Mark. Well, I had better go.

My day needs to get better.

~Claire

It's 17 days till my 17th birthday. That makes me really happy.

I love Kevin very much.

Well, this is really short...

Life bites,
Claire

My life what is left to you? As I sit here in my little world, oblivious to all, I begin to question... why me God? Why did you choose me to do the things I did, and live through the torment and pain that I have. No matter where I run, my past haunts me ever so clearly. If I hide, it's futile. If I accept it, I run? Why?

Have I always been a fighter, and a runner. I will stand up for something if I feel passionately enough about it, but as of lately, I have no emotion. There is nothing. I am an empty shell. Sometimes people change for the good, other times they change for the bad. I think I am caught in-between. As I am typing this, I am listening to 'On That Day Five Years' Ago from Final Fantasy 7.

Well, I might as well stop this damnable thing before I end up typing a book for however wants to read this...

~Claire

Okay. I am really happy. Other than the fact that it's really cold, hinotama_dragon walked me to OTC this morning. I really happen to be fond of him... a lot. 

I am in the middle of trying to look of something on a information system for a 1989 Mercury Sable.

I am almost done with class. I get to leave at 10:20!!!

I get to see hinotama_dragon soon! yay! It's 10:20, so I am outta here!

Love you hinotama_dragon!

I'll try to make this short. I finally made a move on Kevin, courtesy of his cousin, and he said... yes! It made me really really happy, cause I like him a lot. I am really glad that he did. I gave him a hug, and it freaked him out a little, so I think I am going to give him a lot of time. I'll be willing to give him as much time, as he needs, or wants.

Well, I have to go to a PTA meeting with my mom here in about 10 minutes, and I am really bored.

I like you Kevin!!!

I'm in the middle of my OTC class, bored out of my mind. 
I am supposed to be changing a rear suspension strut on the 88 Honda Accord.

I have a major crush on Kevin, but I think he knows that considering that I told him when he walked with me to OTC. Well, I have to go.
